Home > Employees > Overview
Overview









BenefitsERS members have access to a variety of medical and optional benefits. Health BenefitsLearn how ERS can help take care of you and your loved ones.  Optional BenefitsInformation about life insurance and optional benefits.   View frequently asked questions about insurance >  Information on opting out of health coverage > New EmployeeWelcome to the Texas Employees Group Benefits Program (GBP). Discover what benefit choices you should make and when. More about New Employee >Change Your BenefitsOnce per year, you have the option to change your benefits choices. Qualifying life events allow you to make benefits changes during the plan year, like marriage, children, moving, and more. More about Qualifying Life Events >Planning for RetirementYour retirement may be right around the corner or a few decades away. It's never too early to start planning. Learn more about how ERS can help prepare you for life during retirement.  View Eligibility          Find out when you can retire and how different service types can get you there sooner.  Benefits in Retirement          Several benefits are still available to you and your family after you retire. View frequently asked questions about retirement > Who is Eligible for Benefits?ERS administers insurance benefits for employees and eligible family members. 




















