Home > Employees > Retirement Planning > Your ERS Retirement
Your ERS Retirement









You contribute a portion of your salary each month into a retirement account that ERS manages and invests for you. Your retirement program is a defined benefit plan.    EligibilitySee how your service and age work together to make you eligible to retire.        Service CreditYour service credit counts towards your ERS retirement eligibility.Create a retirement estimateAround your birthday, you are sent a Statement of Retirement Benefits. Personalize your estimate online. Benefits during retirementReview the benefits available to you and your family during retirement.        State insurance contributionApplies to members with less
than five years of participation in the Group Benefits Program (GBP) before September 1, 2014. View frequently asked questions about retirement > Purchasing Service CreditFind out how much it will cost to purchase withdrawn or additional service credit. Send in your request for service credit cost > Texa$averSM 401(k) and 457 ProgramTexa$aver is a voluntary retirement savings program that helps you save for your future today. New state employees are automatically enrolled at 1% of their monthly salary.     More about Texasaver and investing for retirement > Applying for RetirementYou should contact ERS no earlier than 90 days before your planned date of retirement. Follow these easy steps > Retirement AccountsERS administers the    retirement accounts for:State employees,LECOS Retirement,ESO Retirement, andJudical Retirement.Does not include Teacher Retirement System employees, TMRS and TCDRS. View the types of retirement ERS administrates > 




















