Employees Retirement System of Texas - Wikipedia






















 






Employees Retirement System of Texas

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search





Employees Retirement System of Texas


Employees Retirement System of Texas (ERS) is an agency of the Texas state government.
ERS was created in 1947. It oversees retirement benefits of state employees. It is headquartered at 200 E 18th Street in Austin.[1]
References[edit]



^ "ers - Benefiting Texans since 1947." Employees Retirement System of Texas. Retrieved on April 14, 2009.



External links[edit]


